HEADWORD: Duograph
<hw>Du"o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>duo</ets>
two + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Photo-engraving)</fld> <def>A
picture printed from two half-tone plates made with the screen set at
different angles, and usually printed in two shades of the same color or
in black and one tint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

